The Covid-19 precautions at this location are subpar. Also, they need to do something about that metal handle door that everyone has to pull by the handle to come in - either install automatic sliding doors (at both the order point and the pick up point!), or keep those doors open during business hours.  Those are crucial points.  Offering a touch-less sanitizer dispenser would be a good  idea as well. (As for coffee, it’s good, as all Starbucks coffees are.  But not worth it to risk getting infected.)
